# Multi-agent session locks (ephemeral — not committed)
.agent/engines/*/session.lock

# Per-session rolling context — ephemeral, per-archive, NOT shared across cluster branches.
# Cross-archive contamination root cause: these files were tracked in the monorepo git;
# Stage-6 rebases brought another archive's session entries into this clone.
# Untracked 2026-06-02 (Command Session — see ops(mailbox-system): hardening commit).
# Each archive manages its own session-context.md locally without git.
.agent/memory/session-context.md
.agent/memory/session-context-archive.md

# .agent/ scratch / research / audit files — per-archive operational scratch.
# These accumulate during sessions and should never replicate across archives via rebase.
# Pattern: uppercase-initial files in .agent/ root + archive/ subdir.
.agent/AEC-*.md
.agent/AUDIT-*.md
.agent/BENCH-*.md
.agent/CHECKLIST-*.md
.agent/RESEARCH-*.md
.agent/SKETCH-*.md
.agent/STAGING-*.md
.agent/SURVEY-*.md
.agent/TODO-*.md
.agent/AUTO-TODO.md
.agent/archive/

# Mailbox state — per-archive, never tracked in canonical
# (canonical-tracked mailbox files were the root cause of cross-archive
# contamination — see conventions/mailbox-scope-discipline.md)
.agent/inbox.md
.agent/outbox.md
.agent/inbox-archive.md
.agent/outbox-archive.md
.agent/outbox_copy.md
.agent/outbox/

# Symlinks to external vendored sources — not committed
vendor-sel4-project/tools
vendor-sel4-project/kernel

# vendor-sel4-tools build artifacts
vendor-sel4-tools/elfloader-tool/build/

# Standalone-workspace library crate lockfiles
# Library crates don't commit Cargo.lock per Rust convention.
# Binary crates (system-udp, moonshot-toolkit) DO commit their lockfiles.
# Resolves 2026-05-30 cleanup-log open question.
system-core/Cargo.lock
system-ledger/Cargo.lock
